DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       ttddll is a facility that will list and add to the to do list
       databases created by xxvvttddll((LL)) Its various options make  it
       easy to use and flexible.  Its primary use is to list todo
       lists from a  non-window  interface.   It  can  easily  be
       placed  in  cron  databases or executed from shell startup
       scripts.

       Note  that  ttddll  reads  and  processes  the  ".xvtdlrc"  X
       resource  database.   This  means  that  defaults  set  up
       through xxvvttddll((LL)) will be used without further intervention
       by ttddll..

       The  user  is  referred  to xxvvttddll((LL)) for the definition of
       terms and understanding of how to  completely  create  and
       manipulate todo list databases.

OOPPTTIIOONNSS
       -add   This  begins  a  dialog  with  the user directed at
              adding an entry to the specified  database  (or  to
              the  default  database  if none specified).  Except
              for the  "-f"  options,  all  other  arguments  are
              ignored when the program encounters a "-add".

       -all   This specifies that all categories are to be listed
              together (default).

       -categories
              This lists the names of categories in the todo list
              database   given.    Subcategories   are  given  as
              indented from their parents.  All  options,  except
              for  the  "-f" option, are ignored when this option
              is given.

       -category catname
              Use the category "catname" rather  than  all  cate-
              gories for listing.

       -date date
              List  the  date specified as "date" rather than the
              current date. This is given in "mm/dd/yy" format.

       -deadline
              Normally, ttddll will not check deadlines when examin-
              ing items for listing.  Specifying this option will
              force ttddll to check the deadline of each  item  when
              examined for listing.




