              Note  that  using  this option could be an inconve-
              nience.  For example, if a deadline  action  is  to
              mail  a message after the deadline, and the current
              date is after the deadline, checking the list  with
              deadline checking several times a day can result in
              several mail messages.

       -f file
              Use "file" instead of $HOME/.tododb

       -help  This will print a usage message and quit.

       -include
              When printing the list, include checked items.  The
              default is not to include these items.

       -list  List  the database for a particular date (default).

       -print Print the database for a particular date.

       -printer printer
              Print  the  list  on  the  printer  "printer".  The
              default is "lp".

       -postscript
              Print  the list in PostScript form.  The default is
              to print  the  list  prepared  for  a  plain  ASCII
              printer.

       -scale factor
              Scale  the  PostScript  output by the integer "fac-
              tor".  Ignored if the "-postscript" option  is  not
              used.

FFIILLEESS
       $HOME/.tododb
              This is the default to do list database.

       /tmp/xvtdl*
              When printing, this temporary file is used to store
              the list prior to sending to the printer.

